cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a non-uniform deployment scheme for small cell networks and analyzes the downlink coverage and single user throughput. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper provides an analytical framework to characterize the coverage and throughput performance of the proposed scheme. This involves the use of information theory concepts and techniques.
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the deployment and performance analysis of small cell networks, which is a topic of interest in the field of communications and networking.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a deployment scheme for small cell networks, which can be viewed as a control problem. The analysis of the coverage and throughput performance also involves system-level considerations.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of small cell networks to meet the forecast data-traffic demand, which is related to multimedia applications and services.
